{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Abolish Homework in all schools",
        "additional_details": "A survey conducted by Stanford university found 56% of students considered that homework is a primary source of stress, and that too much homework could result in the following: lack of sleep, headaches, exhaustion, and finally weight loss.\r\n\r\nHomework deprives youngsters the right to leisure. Article 31 of the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child states the following: \u201cThat every child has the right to rest and leisure, to engage in play and recreational activities.",
        "background": "Homework is draconian and was originally intended as a punishment to those who misbehaved in the classroom and was conducted to do the homework at home as a form of punishment.\r\n\r\nIn modern society it should not exist especially with mental health becoming a greater concern.",
